<!-- Privacy policy -->
<header>
  <%= render "privacy_policy_hero_banner" %>
</header>
<div class="container">
  <main>
    <section>
      <p class="my-5">
        Your privacy is important. This Privacy Policy explains what information is collected and how it is used on
        <%= link_to "www.louisbourne.me", root_path, class: "text-decoration-none fw-medium" %>.
      </p>
    </section>
    <section class="mb-5">
      <h2 class="mb-4 mt-5">1. Information Collected</h2>
      <ul class="mb-0">
        <li><span class="fw-semibold">Contact Form:</span class="fw-semibold"> When you submit the contact form, you provide your name, email address, and message. This information is used only to reply to your inquiry.</li>
        <li><span class="fw-semibold">Browsing:</span class="fw-semibold"> You can view the Site, read the blog, view projects, and download the resume without providing any personal information.</li>
        <li><span class="fw-semibold">Admin Account:</span class="fw-semibold"> Only one account exists for administrative purposes, accessible solely by the Site owner (Louis Bourne).</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
    <section class="mb-5">
      <h2 class="mb-4 mt-5">2. Use of Information</h2>
      <p class="mb-0">
        Information collected through the contact form is used exclusively for direct communication with you.
        It will not be shared, sold, or disclosed to third parties unless required by law.
      </p>
    </section>
    <section class="mb-5">
      <h2 class="mb-4 mt-5">3. Data Storage and Security</h2>
      <p class="mb-0">
        Messages may be stored securely within the Site's database or email system.
        Reasonable security measures are applied to protect this data, though no system is entirely immune to breach.
      </p>
    </section>
    <section class="mb-5">
      <h2 class="mb-4 mt-5">4. Cookies and Analytics</h2>
      <p class="mb-3">
        <%= link_to "www.louisbourne.me", root_path, class: "text-decoration-none" %> uses only essential cookies required for core functionality, such as session management in this standard Rails application. There are <span class="fw-semibold">no advertising cookies and no third-party advertising or social-media trackers</span>.
      </p>
      <p class="mb-0">
        For privacy-friendly, aggregate analytics the Site uses <span class="fw-semibold">PostHog</span> in a fully <span class="fw-semibold">cookieless</span> mode: it sets <span class="fw-semibold">no cookies and uses no localStorage</span> (data is kept only in memory for the duration of your visit). It records aggregate visitor activity such as page views and a few interaction events (for example, downloading the resume or submitting the contact form) to help improve the Site. No individual visitor is personally identified, and the Site owner (Louis Bourne) is excluded from this analytics entirely.
      </p>
    </section>
    <section class="mb-5">
      <h2 class="mb-4 mt-5">5. External Links</h2>
      <p class="mb-0">
        Blog posts or project pages may include links to other websites.
        Louis Bourne is not responsible for the content or privacy practices of those external sites.
      </p>
    </section>
    <section class="mb-5">
      <h2 class="mb-4 mt-5">6. Your Rights</h2>
      <p class="mb-0">
        If you have submitted a message through the contact form, you can request deletion of that correspondence
        by contacting the Site owner directly.
      </p>
    </section>
    <section class="mb-5">
      <h2 class="mb-4 mt-5">7. Changes</h2>
      <p class="mb-0">
        This Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time. Updates will be posted on this page with the date of last modification.
      </p>
    </section>
    <section class="text-center mt-5 pt-5 border-top border-secondary-subtle">
      <p class="text-muted mb-0">
        Questions about privacy?
        <%= link_to "Contact Louis Bourne", root_path(anchor: "contact"), class: "text-decoration-none fw-medium" %>.
      </p>
    </section>
  </main>
</div>
